{"version":"1","action":"add"}{"token":"c96290a2478d0a1916284438ea2c59a1215fe768a87648d04d45f6b7ecb82c3f","parentid":"13","comment":"\u003e \u003e what would be the point of a wallet \"distrusting\" the draft key (technical point 6)?\n\u003e \n\u003e It allows the stakeholders to override the ability to spend from the treasury in the case of compromise of the key.\n\nSorry I don't follow how does it work. Once the pi draft key is included in consensus as the one that can craft the draft tx, the only two options to \"distrust\" it are 1) voting No for tx singed with it, or 2) voting to change consensus again to use another key. If clients are locally configured to \"distrust\" the draft key, what does it influence?\n\n\u003e OP_TGEN and OP_TSPEND create what is effectively an account for the treasury instead of using the standard utxo model\n\nThat was not clear at all. How will it work? Will OP_TGEN increase the treasury's \"account balance\" instead of sending unspend outputs to its address? Will existing treasury balance (currently composed of a ton of small outputs) migrate to this single \"account\" balance?","signature":"4ff9d3d6df4c5d8796b32301bddc7e31211f73be688072044f11256c24cc2059da20ff6204c344338bbe230f9e91aad9ee1872b37ca21cb55395b01756c22202","publickey":"a717216ef1999f84d71aec664b4d14f90616a09b67c7c68892b8e8fe9e8b1441","commentid":"20","receipt":"9711849f6eb5cca9310d219933b08de42eb50ee0035f0f044cd6394a33c8593db037c3cfb53dfb6ef91dd825c89d95abaa74d369e067f4d45324ca8f7f48df08","timestamp":1555230171,"totalvotes":0,"resultvotes":0,"censored":false}
{"version":"1","action":"add"}{"token":"c96290a2478d0a1916284438ea2c59a1215fe768a87648d04d45f6b7ecb82c3f","parentid":"9","comment":"\u003e how about using the extended vote bits to signal approval/disapproval of individual outputs of the TSPEND tx?\n\nI thought similar. If voters can specify line items they don't like when casting No vote, this could reduce the amount of back and forth when disputing the large spending tx. These \"I don't like items X, Y, Z\" would not be processed by consensus, rather signal to Pi admins how to construct a replacement tx. Alternatively these signals can be posted off-chain, voters would need to sign the signals with keys from their tickets that voted No on the spend tx.\n\nThere was a [similar idea](https://github.com/xaur/decred-issues/issues/118) for Politeia proposals.","signature":"a5aea2d1ed7445c3619638197f07d2ea9d714a935e3fcbc890d3d1149f1fa289f0fb82ac558925e1d28d46e1c8ad134840d5a64a4831789d7eb0fc53cb890305","publickey":"a717216ef1999f84d71aec664b4d14f90616a09b67c7c68892b8e8fe9e8b1441","commentid":"21","receipt":"a1ece0c21f19c63c7c45365ad7bc8847ca83e91e890429b181ae470baf616c50dcbb7699203e39ed77e3ccd8628a20a606a195e05817783137dd19cc01f20502","timestamp":1555230298,"totalvotes":0,"resultvotes":0,"censored":false}
{"version":"1","action":"add"}{"token":"c96290a2478d0a1916284438ea2c59a1215fe768a87648d04d45f6b7ecb82c3f","parentid":"4","comment":"\u003e If stakeholders veto a draft treasury spend, which starts some kind of dispute resolution process and requires another vote, that could cause further disruption in pay that many contractors cannot absorb\n\nPay volatility is a problem for me too. Put simply, not getting the money you billed for is a problem if you can't afford the gamble.\n\nReducing the delay between the end of the billing period (end of month) and the payment reduces the impact of volatility. But to really solve it there must be a mechanism to offer stable pay for desired part of the wage. If that is achieved, the delay can be longer. I can wait another week or two while the spending tx is debated, but I need to get what I bill for.","signature":"bf1a6ced711087a5450ff410ef311288a2abe85a9eac08f43de147ba39cfbb36311425609dc40aeed8596e5a3202181931bb6c51164434c491a84ee8297ace05","publickey":"a717216ef1999f84d71aec664b4d14f90616a09b67c7c68892b8e8fe9e8b1441","commentid":"22","receipt":"d97a62828030d917637a26cdb8b6c15c585cf52661aeed83d5fa6f49c1c0892586a302fa04b611bf54a8dfd3de24c1074c5c0cd6f403e987a6ff12a1aada7b0b","timestamp":1555230806,"totalvotes":0,"resultvotes":0,"censored":false}
