{"version":"1","action":"add"}{"token":"c96290a2478d0a1916284438ea2c59a1215fe768a87648d04d45f6b7ecb82c3f","parentid":"19","comment":"Fixing what some contractors don't view as a problem is a challenging problem.\n\nThe reason that the average exchange rate over the month the work is performed and invoiced for is that it provides a much more difficult to game method.  I paid out using spot rates in 2016 and it was quite a mess, and it creates strange incentives, e.g. groups colluding to drive down the price for a low spot rate.\n\nOne of the goals of the contractor management system (CMS) is to lower this time between billing and payout.","signature":"d2a056d63af0abcdd083809bddfd8af622b8dc06ce73c7d66e30544aa738fa573cb39f6cba886bf07fc06470468cc7ae1e83657a1f6dcd16e2ad5b841828c20c","publickey":"e575447e1acb624bedb7c7934f291e3c1b51bb7223f2c06647e551e4cf93f360","commentid":"34","receipt":"88fa1259f871279a32b9fb4a4f6a5bd013aa98ae39c4e1b9132c05004c938bf5b9e479981ca8ee323539aa2f9f58354cb71eb327a7a16af705701bda63a3b804","timestamp":1557161437,"totalvotes":0,"resultvotes":0,"censored":false}
